Citation.sAbstract: The enthalpies of dilution of aqueous solutions of N-acetyl-N -methyl-l-glycinamide (AcGlyNHCH3),  N-acetyl-N -methyl-l- -alaninamide (AcAlaNHCH3),N-acetyl-N -methyl-l- -valinamide (AcValNHCH3),  N-acetyl-N -methyl-l- -leucinamide (AcLeuNHCH3) (BACHEM) and N-acetyl-N -methyl-l- -serinamide  (AcSerNHCH3), N-acetyl-N -methyl-l- -threoninamide (AcThrNHCH3), in water at 298.15K have been  measured. These data were used to calculate the homogeneous enthalpic pair interaction coefficients  based on McMillan Mayer s theory.
Citation.sTitle: Studies of homogeneous interactions of N-acetyl-N-methyl-l-amino acid  amides in water at 298.15
